data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

example: The parents had the child baptized

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 baptise

value.def: When someone is baptized, water is put on their heads or they are covered with water as a sign that their sins have been forgiven and that they have become a member of the Christian Church.

example.ex: At this time she decided to become a Christian and was baptised...
example.tran: 她此时决定成为基督教徒并接受了浸礼。

example.ex: I think your mother was baptized a Catholic.
example.tran: 我想你母亲受洗成了天主教徒。
